This text will check that Lxkeymap can change the keymap
<dl>
    <dt>Click on the lubuntu icon in your panel. Then select "Preferences" and "Lxkeymap"</dt>
        <dd>LXSessions-edit opens in a new window</dd>
    <dt>Enter some words into the testbox, especially addition characters</dt>
        <dd>The input should be according to your keyboard</dd>
    <dt>According to your language, select one keymap with "(dead acute)". Click on apply</dt>
        <dd>The layout has changed. This can be checked at the bottom of the window with "Current keymap"</dd>
    <dt>Try to enter some dead keys (e.g. Â´ ` ^)</dt>
        <dd>The deadkeys show up directly without additional character</dd>
</dl>

